        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 28 at 5:03PM EDT until June 28 at 5:45PM EDT by NWS Baltimore MD/Washington DC</headline>
        <description>SVRLWX

The National Weather Service in Sterling Virginia has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Central Madison County in northwestern Virginia...
South central Rappahannock County in northwestern Virginia...
Northwestern Culpeper County in northern Virginia...

* Until 545 PM EDT.

* At 503 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Madison,
moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Damaging winds will cause some trees and large branches
to fall. This could injure those outdoors, as well as
damage homes and vehicles. Roadways may become blocked by
downed trees. Localized power outages are possible.
Unsecured light objects may become projectiles.

* Locations impacted include...
Culpeper, Madison, Brightwood, Castleton, Criglersville, Catalpa,
Slate Mills, Haywood, Banco, Cardova, Reva, Aylor, Leon, and
Boston.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
